Laptop

Alternatively called a notebook, a laptop is a portable computer that is more efficient and nearly as powerful as a desktop computer. Portable computers run off AC power or batteries such as NiMH, NiCad, or Li-ion packs, for several hours.

Desktops & Monitors

A desktop computer is a personal computing device designed to fit on top of a typical office desk. Desktop computers are commonly used in the enterprise, as well as in consumer use cases such as gaming. In the enterprise, they are important because they are the main means for many users to do their jobs.
